ives of the Hebrew Bible to later Jewish mystical testimonies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aApocalypse of AbrahamxCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aApocalyptic literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aApocryphal books (Old Testament)xCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aTheomachy in the Bible. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Bible Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848090940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438480909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438480909/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles